Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_dont_touch(25.10)                                    set_dont_touch(25.10)

Name
       set_dont_touch - Prevents the specified object from being modified dur-
       ing optimization

Syntax
       set_dont_touch

       <object_list>

       [true | false]

       Prevents  the specified object from being modified during optimization.
       However, the specified object can be moved during optimization.

       When the set_dont_touch command is set to true, the specified nets can-
       not be buffered or become part of the logic  cone  restructuring.  How-
       ever,  you  can  resize the instances connected to this net because the
       set_dont_touch attribute does not affect the connected instances.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       true | false
              Sets or removes the set_dont_touch attribute for  the  specified
              list of objects.

              Default: true

       <object_list>
              Specifies  the  collection  or list of instances, library cells,
              nets, or sub-modules.

Examples
              * The following command prevents the specified instance from be-
                ing modified:

                set_dont_touch [get_cells {TWA/FF1}]

              *

                The following commands prevent the specified  net  from  being
                modified and check the setting with get_property:

                set_dont_touch clk1_net

                get_property [get_nets clk1_net] dont_touch true

              *

                The  following  commands can be used to prevent any ECO inside
                RESULTS_CONV_INST   hierarchical   instance:    set_dont_touch
                [get_cells RESULTS_CONV_INST/*] true

                set_dont_touch [get_nets RESULTS_CONV_INST/*] true

              * The  set_dont_touch  RESULTS_CONV_INST/* true command will re-
                turn [get_cells RESULTS_CONV_INST/*] only. This is because the
                software looks into the first match (type  of  object).  If  a
                match is not found, then the successive objects are searched.

